                </div>
                <p>The biggest change, and the one most likely to excite performance-oriented buyers, will be the significant upgrade to the chassis and suspension components. This is where Hero can truly differentiate the 2025 model.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Upgraded Suspension System: The USD Leap</span><p>
                <p>The current <span class="font-weight-700">Mavrick</span> uses conventional telescopic forks. To enhance both the visual appeal and the dynamic handling, the 2025 model is strongly expected to feature a switch:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Front Suspension: </span>43 mm<span class="font-weight-700"> USD (Upside Down) Telescopic Forks.</span> USD forks offer superior rigidity and reduced unsprung weight, leading to more precise steering feedback and better handling during spirited riding. This is a common upgrade seen across all rival premium models.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Rear Suspension: </span>Twin shock absorbers with 7-<span class="font-weight-700">step preload adjustability</span>. This tried-and-tested setup will likely receive revised damping to complement the firmer front end, providing a planted and comfortable ride.</li>
                </ul>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Braking Confidence with Enhanced ABS</span></p>
                <p>Braking is non-negotiable for safety, and the <span class="font-weight-700">2025 Mavrick </span>will aim for class-leading confidence:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Brake Setup:</span> The bike will retain its<span class="font-weight-700"> large front disc (320 mm) and rear disc (240 mm). </span>However, the caliper quality or pad material may be upgraded to offer a more progressive and sharper bite.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Dual-Channel ABS: </span>A highly advanced, quick-intervening <span class="font-weight-700">Dual-Channel ABS</span> system will remain standard, ensuring safety under hard braking in unpredictable conditions.</li>
                </ul>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Wheels and Tires</span></p>
                <p>The bike is expected to feature 17-inch alloy wheels both front and rear. However, the tire specification may be upgraded. While it currently runs on CEAT or MRF tires, a premium variant might feature stickier, radial tires to handle the expected bump in power and the better suspension setup, thus maximizing the bike’s new handling capabilities.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Technology and Connectivity: The Smart Road Companion</h3>
                <p>Modern motorcycles are defined by their digital features, and the <span class="font-weight-700">2025 Mavrick</span> must raise its game significantly to match segment standards.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Advanced TFT Console and Navigation</span></p>
                <p>The current Mavrick uses a reverse LCD console. The 2025 model is highly anticipated to upgrade to a <span class="font-weight-700">full-colour, high-resolution TFT (Thin-Film Transistor) display, </span>similar to or even better than the one seen on the X440.</p>
