                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Enhanced Rider Safety Aids</span></p>
                <p>Beyond ABS, the 2025 Mavrick may introduce crucial electronic aids typically reserved for higher segments:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Traction Control (TC): </span>While unlikely to be a cornering TC system, a simple, switchable<span class="font-weight-700"> Traction Control </span>system would be a massive safety boost, preventing wheel spin on slippery surfaces. This would be a major feature addition in this segment.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Multiple Riding Modes: </span>The Mavrick 440 could introduce two or three distinct riding modes
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> (Rain, Road, Sport) </span>that subtly tweak throttle response and traction control intervention, allowing the rider to tailor the bike's behavior to the conditions.</li>
                </ul>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Lighting and Premium Touches</span></p>
